---
import b2b7logo from '../../assets/b2b7.svg?url';
import { websiteTitle } from '../../constants';
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title={'Set up your own ' + websiteTitle}>
	<main class="container max-w-[40rem] px-8 pb-12 md:mx-auto md:px-0">
		<div class="mt-28 flex items-center gap-6">
			<div class="w-[5.75rem]">
				<img class="h-[5.75rem] w-[5.75rem]" src={b2b7logo} alt="B2B7 Logo" />
			</div>
			<div class="flex flex-col">
				<span class="text-[1.75rem]">Set up your own</span>
				<span class="text-4xl">Prompts with Friends</span>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-0 mt-16 text-[1.75rem] leading-8 md:ml-[7.25rem]">Developer friend, hello!</div>

		<div class="ml-0 mt-[3.75rem] text-lg leading-[1.875rem] md:ml-[7.25rem]">
			This is your development copy of <a href="https://promptswithfriends.com/"
				>PromptsWithFriends.com</a
			>, designed to showcase the <a href="https://b2bsaaskit.com/">B2B Saas Kit</a>.
		</div>

		<div class="ml-0 mt-[3.75rem] text-lg leading-[1.875rem] md:ml-[7.25rem]">
			<div>Getting started:</div>
			<ol class="ml-7 list-decimal text-blue-600">
				<li>
					<a href="/setup">Configure Prompts with Friends on your machine üëà</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="/app">Try Prompts with Friends on your machine</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://github.com/fogbender/b2b-saaskit">‚≠ê our open-source repo</a>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-0 mt-[3.75rem] text-lg leading-[1.875rem] md:ml-[7.25rem]">
			<div>
				The kit combines several open-source libraries with a handful of commercial
				services&mdash;all featuring generous free-forever starter plans&mdash;to spin up a
				functional multiplayer (i.e., team-based) application:
			</div>
			<ul class="ml-7 list-disc">
				<li>
					<a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a>, an open-source website assembly framework
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://react.dev/">React</a>, an open-source front-end library
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://tailwindcss.com/">Tailwind CSS</a>, an open-source CSS framework
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://doppler.com/">Doppler</a>, a commercial secrets management service
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://propelauth.com/">PropelAuth</a>, a commercial managed user authentication
					service with focus on B2B
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://supabase.com/">Supabase</a>, an open-source, commercial database service
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://stripe.com/">Stripe</a>, a commercial payments service
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://posthog.com/">PostHog</a>, an open-source, commercial product analytics
					service
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://fogbender.com/">Fogbender</a>, commercial customer support software with
					focus on B2B
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://vercel.com/">Vercel</a>, a commercial hosting and deployment service
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="ml-0 mt-[3.75rem] text-lg leading-[1.875rem] md:ml-[7.25rem]">
			Some of these libraries and services are necessary, others can be can <a href="/eject"
				>ejected</a
			>.
		</div>

		<div class="ml-0 mt-[3.75rem] text-lg leading-[1.875rem] md:ml-[7.25rem]">
			Getting help: <a href="https://github.com/fogbender/b2b-saaskit/issues/new"
				>open an issue on GitHub</a
			> or ping <a href="https://twitter.com/jlarky">@JLarky</a> and <a
				href="https://twitter.com/abs">@abs</a
			> on Twitter
		</div>

		<style>
			a {
				color: #0029ff;
				text-decoration: underline;
			}

			a:visited {
				color: #bc48d9;
			}
		</style>
	</main>
</Layout>
